Project Overview
This project demonstrates a production-grade data engineering workflow using a Medallion Architecture to process over 2.9 million rows of NYC Taxi data. By leveraging DuckDB and Parquet, the pipeline achieves high-performance "Zero-ETL" ingestion directly from cloud storage, transforming raw logs into an executive-level market share dashboard.
 Tech Stack
â€¢	Engine: DuckDB (High-performance SQL OLAP)
â€¢	Language: Python 3.10+
â€¢	Validation: Pydantic (Schema Enforcement & Data Contracts)
â€¢	Visualization: Plotly (Interactive Executive Reporting)
â€¢	Data Format: Apache Parquet (Cloud-native columnar storage)
Data Architecture (Medallion Standard)
1. Data Contract & Validation
Before ingestion, the pipeline implements a Contract-First approach. Using Pydantic, we validate a sample of the remote data to ensure schema integrity. This prevents "downstream poisoning" by catching unexpected source changes before they hit the warehouse. Segmented layers using the Databricks Bronze, Silver & Gold method.
2. Bronze Layer (Raw)
â€¢	Mechanism: Virtual View linking to S3-compatible cloud storage.
â€¢	Strategy: "Zero-ETL" ingestion. We maintain a raw, immutable pointer to the source Parquet files, allowing for full replayability without local storage overhead.
3. Silver Layer (Cleansed)
â€¢	Transformations: Data type casting, timestamp normalization, and record filtering.
â€¢	Logic: We strip out "telemetry noise"â€”such as hardware-glitch dates (e.g., year 2001/2049) and zero-distance tripsâ€”to create a reliable "Source of Truth."
4. Gold Layer (Curated Marts)
â€¢	Analytics: Advanced SQL Window Functions calculate daily revenue efficiency (Revenue per Mile).
â€¢	Benchmarking: Each vendor's performance is benchmarked against a rolling market average to identify operational outliers.
Data Quality & Testing
To ensure boardroom-ready accuracy, the pipeline includes an Automated Quality Gate. This suite runs dbt-style SQL tests to verify:
â€¢	Null Integrity: Ensuring primary keys and financial columns are populated.
â€¢	Business Logic: Flagging impossible values (e.g., costs exceeding 10x market average).
â€¢	Zero-Division Safety: Protecting calculations from erratic "zero-distance" inputs.
Executive Insights
The final output is an interactive Market Share Analysis dashboard.
â€¢	Smoothing: Applied a 3-day rolling average to translate volatile daily spikes into readable business trends.
â€¢	Context: Used a Stacked Area Chart with Unified Hover functionality, allowing stakeholders to see total market volume while instantly comparing individual vendor contributions.
How to Run
1.	Clone the repo: git clone https://github.com/austinmott23/nyc_taxi_pipeline.git
2.	Install dependencies: pip install duckdb pandas plotly pydantic
3.	Execute the notebook: Open pipeline.ipynb and run all cells.

